From 290c724f865b66df194945dad70b7505ad9b4760 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@local>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 16:08:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Stage 0: precompile LESS to CSS, drop client-side less.js

Performance + cleanup. No behavioural/visual change intended.

CSS pipeline
- Compile the 17 referenced .less files to sibling .css and link those with
  rel="stylesheet", replacing rel="stylesheet/less".
- Remove wwwroot/js/Addons/less.js + less.min.js (~536 KB) and the _Layout
  include, so browsers no longer download and compile LESS on every page load.
- .less is kept as the source of truth; .css is generated (regenerate with
  lessc). Remote font @imports are emitted as plain CSS @import, unchanged.
- Drop the tokens-only Variables.css link (it compiled to empty - a no-op).

Program.cs
- Collapse the duplicate AddControllersWithViews() into the single filtered
  registration.
- Replace the wide-open inline UseCors with a config-driven default policy
  (Cors:AllowedOrigins). Falls back to the previous permissive behaviour only
  until that setting is populated, so nothing changes until you lock it down.
